<subSubSection id="EB21802EE3ECA9D57D697A40BB7372DE" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="296CDA43B950A152815F3ABB0596F3F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="86ABC4A34BF330474B8DD9266CF51DF6" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
This 
<taxonomicName id="07D1AFA38DB75E3618353F19ABB75D21" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus species" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="species">Didrepanephorus species</taxonomicName>
is transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="136A1D29DDF4EE548F8D3E43C231720F" authorityName="Wood-mason" authorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EAABB84A654331A0281BDBBAED5E183D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Didrepanephorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
here because of the distinct basal protrusion at the lower margin of mandible, as shown by 
<bibRefCitation id="B57E1A84101D656A3E348D09A17E9B72" author="Nagai, S" journalOrPublisher="Gekkan-Mushi" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="6 - 12" refId="B28" refString="Nagai, S, Hirasawa, H, 1991. Two new species of the genus Didrepanephorus from Southeast Asia. Gekkan-Mushi 239: 6 - 12" title="Two new species of the genus Didrepanephorus from Southeast Asia." volume="239" year="1991">Nagai and Hirasawa (1991)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EB4596D56C39AF70AA752F3A766EADEE" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Judging from the figures of habitus and male genitalia, the records of 
<taxonomicName id="5893ACCFD3E197479257B8FBA848D0FE" genus="F." lsidName="F. birmanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="birmanica">
<emphasis id="FB15E122DFEA9BC3A05416BAC1BC3D68" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">F. birmanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Northwest Thailand (
<bibRefCitation id="86DEF6E5DB779E881C39A9B9C253D1C1" author="Nagai, S" journalOrPublisher="Gekkan-Mushi" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="6 - 12" refId="B28" refString="Nagai, S, Hirasawa, H, 1991. Two new species of the genus Didrepanephorus from Southeast Asia. Gekkan-Mushi 239: 6 - 12" title="Two new species of the genus Didrepanephorus from Southeast Asia." volume="239" year="1991">Nagai and Hirasawa 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="43653A9894D7B4A1B0AE180CE8369BC6" author="Nagai, S" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="145 - 157" refId="B26" refString="Nagai, S, 2004. Two new species and four new subspecies of the Rutelinae from southeast Asia. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology 10 (1): 145 - 157" title="Two new species and four new subspecies of the Rutelinae from southeast Asia." volume="10" year="2004">Nagai 2004</bibRefCitation>
) are considered as 
<taxonomicName id="2549817825C468ABA9C34AD734960757" genus="D." lsidName="D. fukinukii" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="fukinukii">
<emphasis id="20C0BAD407C5FE7F7715F83A637A2708" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">D. fukinukii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
here. Thus, the record of 
<taxonomicName id="1854E1C385825CE1C674F26C83B9B62B" genus="F." lsidName="F. birmanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="birmanica">
<emphasis id="3E9C591AEE4C035755EBABBC5C976E3F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">F. birmanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Thailand should be omitted. 
<bibRefCitation id="532FC50EE662EBCDF68C8F687EFFB669" author="Arrow, GJ" journalOrPublisher="Taylor &amp; Francis, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B2" refString="Arrow, GJ, 1917. The Fauna of British India, Including Ceylon and Burma. ColeopteraLamellicornia part II (Rutelinae, Desmonycinae, and Euchirinae). Taylor &amp; Francis, London" title="The Fauna of British India, Including Ceylon and Burma. ColeopteraLamellicornia part II (Rutelinae, Desmonycinae, and Euchirinae)." year="1917">Arrow (1917</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="492B9E3B8E4E8CA861A09D00EDEDF866" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222931908673907" author="Arrow, GJ" journalOrPublisher="Taylor &amp; Francis, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B3" refString="Arrow, GJ, 1919. Notes on ruteline coleoptera and descriptions of a few new species in the British Museum. The Annals and Magazine of natural History, including Zoology. Botany and Geology Series 9 4(24): 379-385. https://doi.org/10.1080/00222931908673907" title="Notes on ruteline coleoptera and descriptions of a few new species in the British Museum. The Annals and Magazine of natural History, including Zoology. Botany and Geology Series 9 4 (24): 379 - 385." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222931908673907" year="1919">1919</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="4D53B0C77841447F12365A0E1B6AF4CF" author="Muramoto, R" journalOrPublisher="Kogane" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="12 - 16" refId="B21" refString="Muramoto, R, Araya, K, 2000. A new species of the genus Fruhstorferia Kolbe, 1894 from northern Thailand. Kogane 1: 12 - 16" title="A new species of the genus Fruhstorferia Kolbe, 1894 from northern Thailand." volume="1" year="2000">Muramoto and Araya (2000)</bibRefCitation>
partly misinterpreted the taxon 
<taxonomicName id="A914E1EEA3E867BAC492434355AD74F0" genus="F." lsidName="F. birmanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="birmanica">
<emphasis id="34DF2767479DAA4EB41E58377AE05EBE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">F. birmanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and applied the name to a 
<taxonomicName id="14B36607983804C1674A2D00683BCBD3" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus species" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="species">Didrepanephorus species</taxonomicName>
from Chin Hills. The 
<taxonomicName id="B73C17BCFF63D4107B60C00F144D26B9" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Didrepanephorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Didrepanephorus species" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="species">Didrepanephorus species</taxonomicName>
from Chin Hills appears to be very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="86A999EE7AE4599FB4F0CDA253CD617D" genus="D." lsidName="D. fukinukii" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="fukinukii">
<emphasis id="607F0D58934CC01F26F96921A9AF7C48" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">D. fukinukii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but having different male genitalia, which has strong incision at outer margin of left paramere.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
